crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This sample is a multi-stage trojan that performs system reconnaissance, exfiltrates the collected data, and downloads and executes a secondary payload. It creates and runs a batch file (`a.bat`) to gather system information (`systeminfo`), process lists (`tasklist`), and directory listings (`dir`), saving the output to a file (`ixeo584.bin`). This data is then exfiltrated via HTTP POST to `trydai.000webhostapp.com/post.php`. Subsequently, it contacts the same C2 server (`/download.php`) to download a payload, which it saves as `netState.dll`, loads into memory, and then deletes from the disk to evade detection.
